References: <AM0PR06MB4611EF288C96185C909229DAA58C9@AM0PR06MB4611.eurprd06.prod.outlook.com>
Message-ID: <MN2PR12MB409477E91C7BAFE15D133040F98C9@MN2PR12MB4094.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

When a package is defuncted and removed from Bioconductor, push access is no longer granted.

The package has been out of Bioconductor for several releases and will have to be re-submitted and undergo a formal review through the submission tracker.

github.com/Bioconductor/Contributions/issues

As stated in the package lifecycle documentation:

bioconductor.org/developers/package-end-of-life/

Cheers,



Lori Shepherd

