References: <BL0PR06MB4178106416E7CEE2E44A2EF4E8879@BL0PR06MB4178.namprd06.prod.outlook.com>
Message-ID: <MN2PR12MB40942769B0C86FF2707FE177F9879@MN2PR12MB4094.namprd12.prod.outlook.com>

The daily build system will build, check, and propagate packages only once per day.  See the top of this page for some information on timing
http://bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/troubleshoot-build-report/


>From the looks of the git.bioconductor.org repo, the changes were only pushed yesterday afternoon and probably not in time to make today's build report.  Most likely the changes will be reflected in tomorrow's build report.  Once tomorrow's build report posts it will have propagated the recent version to allow BiocManager::install to grab the latest (1.0.2) version provided the package built and checked without ERROR.

Cheers,


Lori Shepherd

